---
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
const faqs = [
  { q: 'What is the difference from Remove Extra Spaces?', a: 'Remove Extra Spaces collapses multiple consecutive spaces into one — it keeps single spaces between words. Remove All Whitespace deletes every space, tab, and newline — leaving no whitespace at all.' },
  { q: 'Can I remove only spaces, not newlines?', a: 'Yes — use the checkboxes to selectively remove Spaces, Tabs, or Newlines individually.' },
  { q: 'What is a use case for removing all whitespace?', a: 'Compressing text for hashing, creating compact encodings, removing formatting before processing, or preparing text for character-count comparison without spaces.' },
];
---
<BlogLayout
  title="How to Remove All Whitespace from Text Online Free"
  description="Remove every space, tab, and newline from text. Or selectively remove only spaces, only tabs, or only newlines. Free online whitespace remover."
  canonical="/blog/how-to-remove-all-whitespace-from-text-online"
  date="2026-07-03"
  readTime="3 min read"
  category="Text Utilities"
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <p>Removing all whitespace creates a compact string with no spaces, tabs, or newlines — useful for hashing, encoding, and data processing. This tool lets you remove all whitespace or selectively choose which types to strip.</p>

  <h2>How to Remove Whitespace</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Paste your text.</li>
    <li>Check which whitespace to remove: Spaces, Tabs, Newlines (or all).</li>
    <li>Copy the result.</li>
  </ol>

  <div class="my-8 p-5 bg-violet-950/40 border border-violet-800/50 rounded-2xl text-center">
    <p class="text-slate-300 mb-3">Remove spaces, tabs, and newlines from text — free</p>
    <a href="/tools/remove-whitespace" class="inline-block bg-violet-600 hover:bg-violet-500 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-xl transition-colors">Open Remove Whitespace Tool →</a>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
